A work indeed, ſaith the drooping ſoul; which before it be done, I am like for all this to be undone; 'tis but taking! but opening? a ſad BUT, God knows, for me who am weak, and cannot: Vile, and dare not. Alas what have Dogs to do with Childrens Bread? ſhould I preſume, thinking to believe, and Blaſpheme, thinking to pray;
                              Mat. 15.26. call Chriſt

 my Saviour,Rev. 2.9. and God my Father, and be rejected of both, O whither ſhould I make my ſhame to go? No, no, had I an Hand fit to receive ſuch a Gueſt, gladly would I go through Fire and Water to open the door to Jeſus, and take him with ten thouſand welcomes into my Soul.

